<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1883-10-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1883-10-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="257" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d257">
                    <head>No. 257.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Frelinghuysen</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Hoppin</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1883-10-30"><hi rend="italic">October</hi> 30,
                            1883</date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Frelinghuysen instructed Mr. Hoppin to ascertain and telegraph the
                        regiment in which O’Donnell had served, or the name of the captain of his
                        company.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>